    "created_at": "2016-11-24T01:10:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-24T01:10:44Z",
    "body": "hi @paulcbetts (or i expect there are others who could answer my question),\r\n\r\nif i understand correctly, this issue is still outstanding, and there remains a bug in electron (the bug does not occur in the corresponding version of chrome), but in the mean time we can use\r\n```\r\nsetLayoutZoomLevelLimits()\r\n```\r\nto prevent the zoom from changing back to one on navigation (or the like).\r\n\r\nbut i'm not sure i understand the difference between `setLayoutZoomLevelLimits()` and `setZoomLevelLimits()`. intuitively, i would expect `setZoomLevelLimits` to affect the ... zoom where the *whole* content is scaled up. and `setLayoutZoomLevelLimits()` to affect that other zoom, where only the text size is increased, (and everything reflows).\r\n\r\nif i am correct about these different types of zooms, then does that mean this cannot be used as a work-around for retaining the zoom specified by `setZoomFactor()`?\r\n\r\nthanks for your time."
  },
